  "abilities": [
    {
      "name": "Infiltrators",
      "description": "INFILTRATORS\n\nMany armies employ reconnaissance units who can sit concealed, waiting for the right moment to strike.\nDuring deployment, if every model in a unit has this ability, then when you set it up, it can be set up anywhere on the battlefield that is more than 9\" horizontally away from the enemy deployment zone and all enemy models.",
      "type": "Core",
      "parameter": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Thrill Seekers",
      "description": "If your Army Faction is Emperor’s Children, this unit is eligible to shoot and declare a charge in a turn in which it Advanced or Fell Back, but when doing so:\n\n• It cannot target a unit it was within Engagement Range of at the start of the turn.\n• It cannot target a unit that was the target of another units charge or attack this phase.",
      "type": "Faction",
      "parameter": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Objective Defiled",
      "description": "At the end of your Command phase, if this unit is within range of an objective marker you control, that objective marker remains under your control until your opponent’s Level of Control over that objective marker is greater than yours at the end of a phase.",
      "type": "Datasheet",
      "parameter": null
    },
    {
      "name": "Icon of Excess",
      "description": "At the end of your Shooting phase or the Fight phase, if the bearer’s unit destroyed one or more enemy units that phase, the bearer’s unit takes a Leadership test. If that test is passed, you gain 1CP.",
      "type": "Wargear",
      "parameter": null
    }
  ],
